'''The Dosti Music Project''' is an initiative of [[Found Sound Nation]] and the [[U.S. Embassy in Islamabad]] that began in 2014.<ref>http://www.thewildcity.com/EN/features.xhtml/article/8366-dosti-music-project-a-meaningful-dialogue-with-three-nations</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://newmusicworld.org/event/dosti-music-project-2015/|title=The Dosti Music Project 2015 - New Music World|work=New Music World}}</ref> The project brings together musicians from [[Pakistan]], [[India]] and the [[United States]] for a month-long program to create and record music and then to showcase material on a short tour.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atlanticcenterforthearts.org/dosti-music-project|title=Dosti, Music Project|work=atlanticcenterforthearts.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uno.edu/news/2015/InternationalMusicCollectivetoVisitUNO.aspx|title=International Music Collective to Visit UNO|work=uno.edu}}</ref> Dosti translates to friend in both [[Urdu]] and [[Hindi]], and represents the transcendence of political barriers that the program tries to promote through the musical collaboration.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soundobservatory.com/tickets/2015/3/17/7cfb0ru30tfnwxu7y4iw95quifgo47|title=New Music & New Friends - Saying Goodbye To The Dostis|work=SONO}}</ref>
