The '''Moscow International Automobile Salon''' or '''MIAS''' ({{lang-ru|Московский Международный Автомобильный Салон}}) is the biennial [[auto show]] held at [[Crocus City Mall|Crocus Expo]] in [[Moscow]], [[Russia]]. The show is scheduled by the [[Organisation Internationale des Constructeurs d'Automobiles]], which considers it a major international auto show. The organizers are the Association of Russian Carmakers NP and the Expo Centre. Numerous dealer conferences organized by car producers are forming the integral part of the program. In September 2010, it received the status of 'A' ''High Class Automobile Salon''.
==History== {{Empty section|date=March 2013}}
==2006== The 2006 show was held from 30 August to 10 September.<ref name="mias06">{{cite web |title = Press-release of the Moscow International Automobile Salon 2006 |url = http://eng.interauto-expo.ru/interauto/press/detail_release.php?ELEMENT_ID=8455 |publisher = Crocus Expo |date = 2006-03-13 |accessdate = 2012-09-09 }}{{dead link|date=February 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
==2008== The 2008 show was held from 26 August to 7 September.
