up|Lifan]] 720 (Russian introduction)<ref name="lifan12">{{cite web | title=Lifan will show five new cars in Moscow motor show | url=http://eng.autostat.ru/news/view/6799/ | publisher=Autostat | date=2012-08-10 | accessdate=2012-08-25 }}</ref> * [[Lifan 320|Lifan Smiley]] (facelift) (Russian introduction)<ref name="lifan12" /> * [[Lifan X60]] (Russian introduction)<ref name="lifan12" /> * [[Mazda6]]<ref>{{cite web | title=All-New Mazda6 Sedan World Premiere at 2012 Moscow Motor Show | url=http://www.mazda.com/publicity/release/2012/201207/120725b.html | publisher=Mazda News Releases | date=2012-07-25 | accessdate=2012-08-24 }}</ref> *[[Mercedes-Benz GL-Class (X166)|Mercedes-Benz GL63 AMG]] *[[Nissan Almera]]<ref>{{cite web | title=NISSAN TO PRODUCE NEW ALMERA IN RUSSIA | url=http://newsroom.nissan-europe.com/EU/en-gb/Media/Media.aspx?mediaid=89260 | publisher=Nissan Newsroom Europe | date=2012-02-27 | accessdate=2012-08-24 }}</ref> * [[Nissan Juke]] with Ministry of Sound edition<ref>{{cite web |title = Nissan Joins Forces with Ministry of Sound to Create New Limited Edition Juke |url = http://carscoop.blogspot.com/2012/08/nissan-joins-forces-with-ministry-of.html |publisher = Carscoop |date = 2012-08-20 |accessdate = 2012-08-25 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120823012322/http://carscoop.blogspot.com/2012/08/nissan-joins-forces-with-ministry-of.html# |archive-date = 2012-08-23 |dead-url = yes |df = }}</ref> * [[Opel Astra]] (facelift)<ref name="opel12">{{cite web | title=Opel celebrates four Moscow world premieres | url=http://media.gm.com/media/intl/en/opel/news.detail.html/content/Pages/news/intl/en/2012/opel/08_16_moscow_world_premieres.html | publisher=GM Media Online | date=2012-08-16 | accessdate=2012-08-24 }}</ref> * Opel Astra Sedan<ref name="opel12" /> * [[SEAT Toledo]] concept (Russian introduction)<ref>{{cite web | title=SEAT will present a concept car Toledo in Moscow motor show | url=http://eng.autostat.ru/news/view/6787/ | publisher=Autos