'''St. Katherine Greek Orthodox Church''' is an Eastern Orthodox church in [[Burlington, North Carolina]]. The church houses a Greek Language School, the Philoptohos Society, and hosts Burlington's annual Greek Festival.<ref>http://www.yasas.com/greek-orthodox-details.asp?cid=262</ref>
==History== {{close paraphrase|date=September 2015}} St. Katherine's opening Divine Liturgy service was held on November 28, 1971 led by [[Archbishop Iakovos of America]]. Local dignitaries were also in attendance, including Gov. [[Robert W. Scott]]. The church expanded to include a fellowship hall in 1991. On April 28, 2007 St. Katherine's was officially consecrated by the Archdiocese, raising its status from a mission church to a regular parish.<ref>http://www.stkatherine.nc.goarch.org/</ref>
